---
import { AppConfig } from "../../data";
---

<section class="BrandPresentation">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2 class="title">04. Brand Presentation</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <div class="content">
                <p>This is what gets shown to the client.</p>
                <p>A typical presentation deck looks like:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Slide 1: { AppConfig.brand_name } Brand Identity</li>
                    <li>Slide 2: Brand Overview. Who { AppConfig.brand_name } is.</li>
                    <li>Slide 3: Brand Personality. Smart, Reliable, Innovative.</li>
                    <li>Slide 4: Moodboard: Visual direction approved.</li>
                    <li>Slide 5: Logo Concept: Explain thinking behind the logo. Example: They symbol represents growth, intelligence and forward movement.</li>
                    <li>Slide 6: Logo Variations: Full Logo, Icon only, Monochrome.</li>
                    <li>Slide 7: Color Palette: Show colors and Hex codes.</li>
                    <li>Slide 8: Typography: Show font hierachy.</li>
                    <li>Slide 9: Brand Elements: Patterns, icons, graphics.</li>
                    <li>Slide 10: Mockups: Where the brand comes alive (Business cards, website, social media, letterheads, mobile app).</li>
                    <li>Slide 11: Final identity system. Everything together.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>This presentation is what the client reviews and approves.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
